{"title_page": "2013 World Archery Championships \u2013 Men's Individual Recurve", "text_new": "{{2013WorldArcheryChampionships}}\nThe men's individual [[Recurve bow|recurve]] competition at the [[2013 World Archery Championships]] took place from 29 September\u20136 October 2013 in [[Belek]], [[Turkey]].\n\n146 archers from 62 countries entered the competition, with a maximum of three entries per country. The top 104 archers qualified for the knockout tournament, with the top 8 scores in qualifying receiving a bye to the third round. [[2011 World Archery Championships - Men's Individual Recurve|Reigning champion]] [[Kim Woo-Jin]] was not selected as part of the [[South Korea]]n representation.<ref>[http://www.worldarchery.org/Portals/1/Documents/World%20Championships/2013%20Belek/Results/ECOMPC.pdf Entry list]</ref> Nevertheless, for the fifth Championships in succession the title was won by a Korean, in this case 18-year-old [[Lee Seung-Yun]], who in his first season representing Korea defeated teammate, [[Archery at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual|Olympic champion]], [[2013 FITA Archery World Cup|World Cup champion]] and [[World Archery Rankings#Number one ranked archers|world number one archer]] [[Oh Jin-Hyek]] in the final in 5 sets.<ref>[http://www.worldarchery.org/Portals/1/Documents/World%20Championships/2013%20Belek/Results/IQRRM.pdf Official results]</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\nAll times are [[UTC+02:00]].<ref>[http://www.worldarchery.org/Portals/1/Documents/World%20Championships/Comp%20Schedule_Belek%20W%20Ch%202013_V1%203.pdf Competition schedule]</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Date !! Time !! Phase\n|-\n| 29 September 2013 || 14:00 || Official practice\n|-\n| 1 October 2013 || 09:00 || Qualification\n|-\n| 2 October 2013 || 11:15 || 1/48 and 1/24 Eliminations\n|-\n| 3 October 2013 || 09:30 || 1/16, 1/8,  QF and SF Eliminations\n|-style=background:lemonchiffon\n| 6 October 2013 || 16:20 || Medal matches\n|}\n\n==Qualification round==\nPre-tournament world rankings ('WR') are taken from the 28 August 2013 [[World Archery Rankings]].<ref>[http://www.worldarchery.org/en-us/results/worldranking/outdoor.aspx World Archery Rankings]</ref>  Qualification consisted of 4 rounds of 36 arrows, at 90m, 70m, 50m and 30m. This was the last [[World Archery Championships]] in which a 30m round was used in qualification. A three-way shootoff was required to determine 7-9th places.<ref>[http://www.worldarchery.org/Portals/1/Documents/World%20Championships/2013%20Belek/Results/IEFRM.pdf Official brackets]</ref>\n;Key\n{{Color box|#ccccff|border=darkgray}} Bye to third round <br />\n{{Color box|#ccffcc|border=darkgray}} Qualified for eliminations\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:left;\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Archer\n!Score\n![[World Archery Rankings|WR]]\n|- \n|119 ||{{flagathlete|[[Fabian Cardenas]]|ARG}}||'''1218'''||''164''\n|- \n|136 ||{{flagathlete|[[Genaro Riccio]]|ARG}}||''' 1167'''||''135''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|101 ||{{flagathlete|[[Hugo Eduardo Robles]]|ARG}}||'''1247'''||''106''\n|- \n|128 ||{{flagathlete|[[Arshak Petrosyan (archer)|Arshak Petrosyan]]|ARM}}||''' 1193'''||''254''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|34 ||{{flagathlete|[[Matthew Gray (archer)|Matthew Gray]]|AUS}}||''' 1306'''||''416''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|39 ||{{flagathlete|[[Ryan Tyack]]|AUS}}||''' 1299'''||''95''\n|- style=\"background:#ccccff;\"\n|8 ||{{flagathlete|[[Taylor Worth]]|AUS}}||''' 1335'''||''32''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|76 ||{{flagathlete|[[Alexander Bertschler]]|AUT}}||'''1273'''||''n/a''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|88 ||{{flagathlete|[[Raphael Dutzler]]|AUT}}||'''1258'''||''n/a''\n|- \n|127 ||{{flagathlete|[[Erwin Rebernig]]|AUT}}||'''1197'''||''n/a''\n|- \n|108 ||{{flagathlete|[[Muhammed Durul Huda]]|BAN}}||'''1239'''||''404''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|80 ||{{flagathlete|[[Md Ruhan Shana]]|BAN}}||''' 1270'''||''359''